# Zabbix Agent (Docker + Script)

This repository provides two ways to set up **Zabbix Agent 2** on Ubuntu-based systems:

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

*Install via script* (for running directly on a VM/Server)  

* Clone the repository and run the setup script:

1 - git clone https://github.com/r-hadigol/zabbix-agent.git

2 - cd zabbix-agent

3 - chmod +x setup-agent.sh
4 - ./setup-agent.sh  <ZABBIX_SERVER_IP>  <ZABBIX_AGENT_HOSTNAME>

EXAMPLE : ./setup-agent.sh 192.168.1.100 ubuntu-02

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

*Run as a Docker container* (for lightweight deployments)

docker build -t my-zabbix-agent:latest .

docker run -d --name zabbix-agent -e ZBX_SERVER="192.168.1.100" -e HOSTNAME="docker-agent" my-zabbix-agent:latest

